
This directory contains the source code for an example C++
client for ConceptBase. It uses the C++ library libCBview
which should be included in this package. By default,
the program connects to the server on port 4001 on
"localhost".

It should be possible to build this example client with any
C++ compiler (e.g., gcc or Microsoft Visual C++) but there
might problems with the encoding of symbols within the libraries
as this is not standardized. The library libCBview has been
built with gcc 3.2 on Unix and with MS Visual C++ 6.0 on Windows.

Compiler flags:
 - Solaris: -I$(CB_HOME)/include -DSOLARIS
 - Linux: -I$(CB_HOME)/include -DLINUX
 - Windows: -nologo -MT -W3 -GX -O2 -I$(CB_HOME)/include -D "WIN32" -D "NDEBUG" -D "_CONSOLE" -D "_MBCS" -Fo".\\" /Fd".\\" -c

Linker flags:
 - Solaris: -L$(CB_HOME)/sun4/lib -lCB -lCBview -lnsl -lsocket
 - Linux: -L$(CB_HOME)/linux/lib -lCB -lCBview
 - Windows: kernel32.lib user32.lib wsock32.lib $(CB_HOME)/windows/lib/libCB.lib $(CB_HOME)/windows/lib/libCBview.lib \
      -nologo -subsystem:console -incremental:no -machine:I386

For Windows, you have to make sure that the dynamic libraries libCB.dll and libCBview.dll
are found when you execute the example application.


